The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 14 September is 71,723 (8,266.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 09 September, there were 2,083 new confirmed cases (240.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 02 September, there were 2,251 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 7% (168 fewer cases).
